  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. **F&G is useless as a signal right now** \u2014 ALL 161 trades happened during Extreme Fear (F&G 0-19). No data for other regimes. Can't correlate what doesn't vary.\n2. **Monday results: 3W/2L = 60% WR on 5 trades** (outcomes say 5, but logs show 6 executions). All YES bets at hour 11-12.\n3. **Duplicate trade bug is BACK** \u2014 two trades 7 seconds apart at 11:19 (same 5-min window), two more at 11:38-11:39. Per-window guard is broken.\n4. **Hour 19 completely blocked** \u2014 UP price at $0.540 > max_price $0.535. 46 price blocks today. Our second-best hour is being wasted.\n5. **V3.2 filter blocks NO trades at hour 11** \u2014 \"YES-only, NO=40% WR\". Forces us to wait for negative bias to buy YES.\n\n**My thinking:** Two competing problems:\n- max_price at $0.535 is too tight, blocking our best hours \u2192 should widen to $0.545\n- BUT higher price = higher break-even WR needed (54.5% at $0.545)\n- The duplicate trade bug is more urgent \u2014 it doubles our risk per window\n\n**Decision:** Fix duplicate bug first (P2 priority). Widen max_price to $0.545 with data backing needed. F&G not actionable until we trade in non-fear regime.\n\n**Next P4:** Build BTC volatility regime classifier (ATR-based). More useful differentiator than F&G.\n\n## 2026-03-30 20:10 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] 20h = Weakest Active Hour: 60% WR, Zero Signals in Downtrends\n\n**Task:** Analyze 20h signal availability and historical performance.\n\n**Finding:**\n- **20h today: 0/24 negative bias readings.** 100% positive (mean +44.8). No YES opportunities in a down-trending market.\n- **Historical 20h WR: 60% (6W/4L, n=10)** \u2014 lowest of all active hours:\n  - 12h: 83% (n=18, best)\n  - 19h: 73% (n=15)\n  - 11h: 64% (n=11)\n  - 20h: 60% (n=10, worst)\n\n**Why 20h underperforms:**\n- Late US afternoon \u2014 institutional positioning done, retail selling into close\n- In downtrend days: 100% positive bias (sellers dominate) \u2192 no contrarian YES signals\n- In uptrend days: may get signals but edge is weaker than 11-12h\n- Sample size small (10 trades) but directionally concerning\n\n**V5 consideration:** 20h may not be worth keeping as an active hour. Removing it would lose ~1 trade/day on average but could improve overall WR from 55% to 58%+. Need 20+ more 20h trades to confirm \u2014 current n=10 is borderline significant.\n\n**Decision:** Keep 20h active for now (need more data). Flag for V5 review when we have 30+ trades at 20h.\n\n## 2026-03-30 20:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] 20h Active But Bullish: Regime Cleared, Bias Positive\n\n**Task:** Monitor 20h session. Check if regime cleared and analyze signal availability.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Regime: RANGE 2/6 \u2705** \u2014 cleared at ~20:05 (was TREND 3/6 at 20:04). The 4h lookback shift dropped trend from -0.4% to -0.33% and consistency from 0.88 to 0.75.\n\n2. **All",
